ZH: 他是一个清白的人，从未做过任何坏事。
EN: He is an innocent person who has never done anything wrong.

ZH: 她的良心清白，不会做出欺骗他人的事情。
EN: Her conscience is clear and she would never deceive anyone.

ZH: 这位演员因为清白而备受尊敬。
EN: This actor is highly respected because of his innocence.

ZH: 天空的蓝色给人一种清白的感觉。
EN: The blue color of the sky gives a sense of purity.

ZH: 孩子们的心灵是清白的，他们不会背叛父母。
EN: Children's hearts are pure and they would never betray their parents.

ZH: 这个案件中，被告宣称自己是清白的。
EN: In this case, the defendant claims to be innocent.

ZH: 她受到了无辜清白的攻击，但她始终保持沉默。
EN: She was unjustly accused and attacked, but she remained silent.

ZH: 作为一个律师，他一直致力于保护无辜清白的人。
EN: As a lawyer, he has always been dedicated to protecting the innocent.

ZH: 这个故事告诉人们清白的力量是无穷的。
EN: This story tells people that the power of innocence is infinite.

ZH: 在这个黑暗的世界里，他坚持保持自己的清白和善良。
EN: In this dark world, he insists on maintaining his innocence and kindness.

ZH: 她永远都相信自己的父亲是一个清白的人。
EN: She always believes that her father is an innocent person.

ZH: 他坚持自己的清白，拒绝接受那些不公正的指控。
EN: He insists on his innocence and refuses to accept those unjust accusations.

ZH: 这个案件揭示了一个清白的人也可以受到指控。
EN: This case reveals that even an innocent person can be accused.

ZH: 在法庭上，他向陪审团证明了自己的清白。
EN: In court, he proved his innocence to the jury.

ZH: 虽然她被指控犯罪，但她始终坚持自己的清白。
EN: Although she was accused of the crime, she always insisted on her innocence.

ZH: 我们必须相信一个人无辜直到有足够证据证明他的清白。
EN: We must believe a person is innocent until there is enough evidence to prove their innocence.

ZH: 这位被告以自己的清白为辩护，但最终还是被判有罪。
EN: The defendant pleaded his innocence, but ultimately was found guilty.

ZH: 社会应该为保护清白的人提供公平公正的法律程序。
EN: Society should provide fair and just legal proceedings to protect the innocent.

ZH: 这个纯洁的童话故事向孩子们传递了清白和善良的价值观。
EN: This pure fairy tale story conveys the values of innocence and kindness to children.

ZH: 她是一个清白的人，无论发生什么事情，她都保持乐观和豁达。
EN: She is an innocent person who remains optimistic and open-minded no matter what happens.
